HEADWORD: Haemol
<hw>Hae"mol</hw> <pr>(h⟦emac⟧"m⟦omac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>a"i^ma</grk> blood.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A dark brown
powder containing iron, prepared by the action of zinc dust as a
reducing agent upon the coloring matter of the blood, used medicinally
as a hematinic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

